WEBVTT

00:02.883 --> 00:08.109
One of the strong supporters of the Colonel's 
Revolt. Not so much the Colonel's Revolt, but of

00:08.129 --> 00:12.434
what we were trying to do. The objective, which was 
to build an army instead of allowing it to be

00:12.474 --> 00:18.642
destroyed. Well, General Gavin, James M. Gavin, 
who was Chief of Research and Development and

00:19.343 --> 00:32.198
later Chief of Army Operations and Plans, And I was 
very close to General Gavin. I think he was a

00:38.607 --> 00:40.428
wonderful man. You know, he was a major general 
when he was about 30 years old, 31 years old.

00:45.573 --> 00:49.537
Commanded 82nd Division, I guess, 82nd Airborne. 
He was one of the early airborne types. I was

00:54.682 --> 01:01.408
involved in Fort Benning in the early days and 
glider training on the 4X5 type. I was in the second

01:03.886 --> 01:16.742
armored division and didn't go to that side of the 
thing because this armored thing was so

01:03.886 --> 01:16.742
fascinating to me, the mechanization. As you 
know, our armored divisions were patterned after

01:18.104 --> 01:22.870
the German Panzer divisions. The first that we had 
in our country, the first and the second.

01:30.498 --> 01:41.754
Mr. Wilson finally cut him off from the press, cut 
him off from visiting Congress, cut him off from

01:30.498 --> 01:41.754
answering letters to the Congress, and that sort 
of thing. And all the letters that came to him from

01:42.916 --> 01:54.092
the Congress where we were mustering support to 
get an army, to build an army of the future. He was

01:54.325 --> 02:06.240
not permitted to answer, and I would go by each 
morning and pick up his letters and answer them

01:54.325 --> 02:06.240
myself, show him the answers, and sign them off 
myself back to the Congress. So that was a way

02:06.260 --> 02:16.193
around him violating an edict from the White House 
through the Secretary of Defense.

02:20.659 --> 02:23.843
We had a— What specifics? What specific proposals 
did you put forth to the congressman?

02:31.065 --> 02:32.687
We know what Wilson's trying to do. He's trying to 
cut the size of conventional forces and build a

02:33.187 --> 02:39.074
nuclear force and the so-called more bang for the 
buck idea. One specific one was Jupiter C.

02:39.094 --> 02:46.803
Missile. I wanted, and General Gavin wanted to go 
ahead and fire in September the 26th

02:56.746 --> 03:06.656
1956,

02:56.746 --> 03:06.656
and to place in orbit a satellite.

03:11.260 --> 03:14.523
And we were ready to do it, had the capability to do 
it. We'd had some failures with the Navy Vanguard

03:15.324 --> 03:25.774
system, but Jupiter C, which later was Redstone 
Missile, We had a major general, Maderas, down

03:27.661 --> 03:33.026
there, a real sharp ordnance major general. And we 
know where we were going. We needed about $10

03:36.650 --> 03:40.193
million in order to launch.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.283
Eisenhower and Wilson turned us down. We got the 
money in the program. They wouldn't spend it.

04:02.626 --> 04:31.857
next year following the Sputnik was fired and made 
us look like a bunch of asses and uh so this is you

04:02.626 --> 04:31.857
must have got the money after Sputnik oh yes got it 
then sure but you see what you see what I'm talking

